HEADWORD: Gatten tree
<hw>Gat"ten tree`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[Cf. Prov. E. <ets>gatter
bush</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A name given to the small
trees called guelder-rose (<spn>Viburnum Opulus</spn>), cornel
(<spn>Cornus sanguinea</spn>), and spindle tree (<spn>Euonymus
Europ⟦ae⟧us</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gat-toothed</ent>⟦br⟧
